cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on visualizing the intra-class knowledge inside CNN for image recognition tasks. It also involves the use of CNN visualization models, which is a common technique in computer vision research. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as CNN is a type of machine learning algorithm and the paper discusses how CNN separates different classes with learned inter-class knowledge. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper involves understanding how an object class is represented in the fully-connected layers of CNN, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence. 

The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is another possibility as CNN is a type of neural network and the paper discusses how intra-class knowledge is represented in a hierarchical and ensemble way. 

Finally, the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is a possibility as the paper discusses style-based image retrieval and style-based object completion, which are applications related to multimedia.
